<li id="cite_note-23"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-23">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">as detailed in Arguimbau's article</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Vasari-24"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Vasari_24-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Vasari_24-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Vasari_24-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">Giorgio Vasari, <i>Michelangelo</i> from <i>Lives of the Artists</i>,(1568) translated by George Bull, Penguin Classics, (1965) <a href="Special_BookSources/0140441646" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 0-14-044164-6</a></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-RS-25"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-RS_25-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-RS_25-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-RS_25-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation web">Serrin, Richard. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://mimsstudios.com/richardserrinarticle.pdf">"Lies and Misdemeanors, Gianluigi Colalucci's Sistine Chapel Revisted"</a> (PDF)<span class="printonly">. <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://mimsstudios.com/richardserrinarticle.pdf">http://mimsstudios.com/richardserrinarticle.pdf</a></span>.</span></span></li>
</ol>
